Description: Critical Thinking: Students will demonstrate the ability to analyze complex problems and develop evidence-based solutions
Communication: Students will communicate effectively in writing and oral presentations appropriate to their discipline
Quantitative Reasoning: Students will apply mathematical and statistical methods to interpret data and solve problems
Information Literacy: Students will locate evaluate and ethically use information from diverse sources
Global Awareness: Students will demonstrate understanding of diverse cultures and global perspectives
Ethical Reasoning: Students will analyze ethical issues and apply ethical frameworks to decision-making
Teamwork and Collaboration: Students will work effectively in diverse teams to accomplish shared goals
Scientific Reasoning: Students will apply scientific methods to investigate natural phenomena
Creative Expression: Students will demonstrate creative thinking and artistic expression
Civic Engagement: Students will engage responsibly in civic life and contribute to their communities
